bilingual.source: The psychological effects of stress can be severe.
bilingual.target: 压力的心理的影响可能是严重的。

bilingual.source: The movie had a psychological impact on the audience.
bilingual.target: 这部电影对观众产生了心理的影响。

bilingual.source: He went to a psychological counselor to discuss his issues.
bilingual.target: 他去找了一位心理的顾问讨论他的问题。

bilingual.source: The book explores the psychological aspects of human behavior.
bilingual.target: 这本书探讨了人类行为的心理的方面。

bilingual.source: She is studying psychological theories in her university course.
bilingual.target: 她在大学课程中学习心理的理论。

bilingual.source: The documentary shed light on the psychological impact of incest.
bilingual.target: 这部纪录片揭示了乱伦对心理的影响。
心理的进化是不存在的。

bilingual.source: How to solve psychological the seamy side?
bilingual.target: 怎样解决心理的阴暗面?
面子这个词并不具有生理上的含义，而是指一种心理的状态。

bilingual.source: The psychological position is what is relevant.
bilingual.target: 心理的立场是什么是相关的。

list.abstract: Psychological，英语单词，形容词，意思是“心理的；心理学的；精神上的”。

yingyinNormal.en: Trust me, Kripke will fall easy prey to my psychological warfare. Observe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 信我，克里帕奇很快就会倒在我的心理战上的，观察吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Our job today is to analyze your needs, both psychological and physical. Sounds pretty straight forward.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天的任务是分析你的需求心理以及身体两个层面的。直接了当。

yingyinNormal.en: Mmm, in my family, holidays weren't so much celebrated as studied for their anthropological and psychological implications on human society.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在我家，节日通常是用来研究人类社会中它们起到的人类学和心理学意义，而不是用来庆祝的。

yingyinNormal.en: But according to Wendy Troxel, a psychology professor at the University of Pittsburgh, the psychological benefits of co-sleeping outweigh the physical downsides.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但匹兹堡大学心理学教授Wendy Troxel有不同说法，一起睡觉带来的心理好处远大于其在身理上的坏处。

yingyinNormal.en: At first, looking at these harsh realities caused me a lot of pain. But I learned that this pain was just psychological, and that my seeing things differently made all the difference.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一开始，面对血淋淋的现实我非常痛苦。但我意识到这只是心理上的痛苦，我看待事物的方式才最重要。

数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: can bring <highlight>psychological</highlight> benefits
examination_example.sentence_trans: 能带来心理上的好处

examination_example.sentence: This step may sound overly deferential, but it's a smart way to give the powerful person <highlight>psychological</highlight> safety and control.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这一步可能听起来过于恭敬，但这是给有权势的人心理安全和控制的聪明方法。

examination_example.sentence: Visual recognition, reads the study, is "an automatic <highlight>psychological</highlight> process, occurring rapidly and intuitively with little or no apparent conscious deliberation".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项研究表明，视觉识别是“一种自发的心理过程，快速而直观地发生，几乎没有或根本没有明显的刻意思考”。

examination_example.sentence: Because humans have an inherent need to resolve uncertainty, according to a recent study in <highlight>Psychological</highlight> Science.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 《心理科学》最近的一项研究表明，该问题的原因是人类具有解决不确定性的内在需求。

examination_example.sentence: This has created "a paradox", according to the depressing beginning of a paper forthcoming in the journal <highlight>Psychological</highlight> Science.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据即将在《心理科学》杂志上发表的一篇令人沮丧的论文的开头，这样的现状已经形成了“矛盾的现状”。

examination_example.sentence: Electronic devices and excessive time spent online may have reversed these trends in recent years, causing problems for young people's <highlight>psychological</highlight> health.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 近几年电子设备和在网上花费过多的时间可能已经扭转了这些趋势，从而给年轻人的心理健康造成了问题。

examination_example.sentence: Rarely has there been a better example of the power of attitude, one of our most powerful <highlight>psychological</highlight> tools.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 态度的力量是我们最强大的心理工具之一，很少有比这更好的例子能说明它的力量。

examination_example.sentence: The researchers conclude that electronic communication was the only adolescent activity that increased at the same time <highlight>psychological</highlight> wellbeing declined.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员得出结论，电子通讯是唯一的随着青少年使用的增加，同时会伴随心理健康的下降的活动。

examination_example.sentence: Their <highlight>psychological</highlight> trickery will work to help keep farmers from shooting lions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的心理骗术将有助于阻止农民射杀狮子。

examination_example.sentence: Decision fatigue is a <highlight>psychological</highlight> phenomenon that takes a toll on the quality of your choices after a long day of decision making.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 决策疲劳是一种心理现象，在做了一整天的决策后，会对你的选择质量造成影响。

examination_example.sentence: Numerous <highlight>psychological</highlight> studies have demonstrated that children who learn to wait for things they desire are more likely to succeed later in life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 无数心理学研究已经表明，学会等待自己想要的东西的孩子在以后的生活中更有可能取得成功。

examination_example.sentence: Smartphone-based data collection comes at an appropriate time in the evolution of <highlight>psychological</highlight> science.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 基于智能手机的数据收集正值心理学科学发展的适当时机。

sense_info_list.zh: 心理的; 精神现象的

examination_example.sentence: He thinks that being a close loser might give people a <highlight>psychological</highlight> boost, or the proverbial kick in the pants.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他认为，一个差点就成功的人可能会受到一种心理上的鼓舞，或者是鞭策。

examination_example.sentence: It's a <highlight>psychological</highlight> phenomenon.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是一种心理现象。

examination_example.sentence: How college students can handle their <highlight>psychological</highlight> problems?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大学生如何处理他们的心理问题？

examination_example.sentence: One widely accepted <highlight>psychological</highlight> definition of boredom is "the distasteful experience of wanting, but being unable, to engage in satisfying activity."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个公认的对无聊的心理学定义是“想要参与令人满意的活动但又不能参与，由此带来的令人不快的体验。”

examination_example.sentence: When are people likely to experience boredom, according to an accepted <highlight>psychological</highlight> definition?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据公认的心理学定义，人们在什么时候可能会感到无聊?

examination_example.sentence: Whether you can successfully change your personality as an adult is the subject of a longstanding <highlight>psychological</highlight> debate.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为一个成年人你是否能成功地改变自己的性格，这是一个长期存在的心理学论题。

examination_example.sentence: Call <highlight>psychological</highlight> (心理的) hotline to share your worries and get help from others going through the same experience.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拨打心理热线，分享你的担忧，并从其他有同样经历的人那里获得帮助。

examination_example.sentence: Understanding <highlight>psychological</highlight> time makes life pass more quickly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 了解心理时间会让生活过得更快。

examination_example.sentence: One basic law of <highlight>psychological</highlight> time is that time seems to slow down when we’re exposed(接触) to new environments and experiences.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 心理时间的一个基本规律是，当我们接触到新的环境和经历时，时间似乎会变慢。
